## PRIOR FINDINGS (build on these; do NOT duplicate; you MUST surface >=1 that these missed)
- F-14-4 [unnamed/P1] compiled-route.cjs fails safe to a legacy sentinel on ANY resolver error including a moved or archived spec tree, with no stderr, log, or telemetry — an invisible fleet-wide rollback if 007-unified-refactor-implementation is archived during the 019 program cutover
- F-14-5 [activation/P1] The fence epoch is incremented on both forward flip and rollback (flip-serving.cjs:128 and 105), so the fence value alone cannot tell an operator whether the current state was reached by cutover or by recovery — defeating P4 audit reconstruction
- F-14-6 [unnamed/P1] The launcher's .env/.env.local loader (mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs:70-76) runs at module top-level and injects into process.env, but createChildEnv() (line 267) filters through CHILD_ENV_ALLOWLIST (line 99-150) which omits SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING, so the standard 'put it in .env' operator path silently strips the flag from the spawned advisor child
- F-18-1 [playbooks/P0] Lane C live mode does not execute the manual playbook command, evidence, or pass-fail contract because sk-doc scenarios are loaded with null pass criteria and noncritical status.
- F-18-2 [sk-doc-templates/P1] The playbook skill limits scenario verdicts to PASS, FAIL, and blocked SKIP while its root template permits PARTIAL and can declare READY with noncritical partial scenarios.
- F-18-3 [archiving/P0] The current live executor dispatches a reasoning variant but records only the model, so archived output cannot prove the required GPT-5.6 LUNA HIGH configuration.
- F-18-4 [archiving/P1] The benchmark runner overwrites an existing caller-selected report pair even though the durable storage contract declares every run label immutable.
- F-18-5 [activation/P0] Existing real-model acceptance declares completion despite LUNA transport failures, so zero wrong-hub routes is not an all-LUNA-pass criterion.
- F-18-6 [benchmark/P1] Prior LUNA routing evidence contains no gold-bearing holdouts and therefore establishes fitted-prompt behavior rather than routing generalization.
- F-18-7 [unnamed/P1] The raw log records a completed post-flip sweep while the sibling runtime summary still says that sweep was not rerun.
- F-19-1 [catalogs/P0] Six of the seven compiled-eligible hubs lack the canonical hub-root catalog required before a compiled-routing leaf can be added without creating a misleading partial inventory.
- F-19-2 [sk-doc-templates/P1] The exact per-feature contract is the entire scaffold, including source and validation tables, rather than a root-catalog paragraph or abbreviated router note.
- F-19-3 [activation/P0] Catalog current-reality wording cannot claim default-on before P4 because the shipped advisor still enables enrichment only when SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING equals 1.
- F-19-4 [catalogs/P0] Final catalog source tables cannot comply with the stable-source rule while resolver and activation authority still live under mutable spec history.
- F-19-5 [sk-doc-templates/P1] The per-feature template claims trigger phrases drive advisor routing, but the live document harvester excludes feature-catalog directories by scanning only references and assets.
- F-19-6 [catalogs/P1] Existing validation cannot prove catalog completeness and treats off-taxonomy validation types as warnings rather than blocking failures.
- F-20-1 [unnamed/P0] The OpenCode hook drops the advisor's compiledRoute before rendering and injecting its system brief, so default-on cannot make compiled routing effective at that agent boundary.
- F-20-2 [activation/P0] The supported bridge-to-launcher fallback has a second child-environment allowlist that omits SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING, so an explicit future =0 kill-switch is lost before the advisor child starts.
- F-20-3 [activation/P1] The OpenCode advisor cache fingerprints skill roots and advisor artifacts but not activation manifests, so a serving flip, rollback, or re-mint will not invalidate a future compiled-routing hook decision.
- F-20-4 [unnamed/P1] The OpenCode plugin regression suite stubs opaque bridge output and therefore cannot detect compiledRoute loss or kill-switch propagation through the real hook chain.
- F-21-1 [playbooks/P0] Legacy route, holdout, and disambiguation cases are behavior-identical under compiled serving, so the new matrix should test serving authority rather than duplicate routing semantics.
- F-21-2 [playbooks/P0] The minimal complete hub matrix is seven primary scenarios selected by distinct route shape: sk-code surfaceBundle, three generic ordered bundles, sk-prompt default routing, and the explicit sk-design and sk-doc bundle rules.
