   228	## L2: PHASE DEPENDENCIES
   229	
   230	```text
   231	Operator go-ahead to begin
   232	        |
   233	        v
   234	P0 governance + observability
   235	        |
   236	        v
   237	P1 drift CI -----> P2 one-profile canary
   238	        |                 |
   239	        +--------+--------+
   240	                 v
   241	         P3 derived eligibility
   242	                 |
   243	                 v
   244	         P4 staged default-on
   245	```
   246	
   247	| Phase | Depends On | Blocks |
   248	|-------|------------|--------|
   249	| P0 | Operator go-ahead to begin | P1, P2 |
   250	| P1 | P0 status classification and stable resolver decision | P3, P4 |
   251	| P2 | P0 observability and named canary profile | P3, P4 |
   252	| P3 | P1 green and P2 canary evidence | P4 |
   253	| P4 | P0-P3 green, sibling alignment phases available | None |
   254	<!-- /ANCHOR:phase-deps -->
   255	
   256	---
   257	
   258	<!-- ANCHOR:effort -->
   259	## L2: EFFORT ESTIMATION
   260	
   261	| Phase | Complexity | Relative Effort |
   262	|-------|------------|-----------------|
   263	| P0 governance, observability, resolver remediation | High | Largest design and harness change |
   264	| P1 drift CI | Medium | One deterministic gate plus CI wiring |
   265	| P2 canary | Medium | Bounded profile configuration and evidence |
   266	| P3 eligibility | High | Two consumers move to one derived predicate |
   267	| P4 staged cutover | High | Seven sequential gates with rollback evidence |
   268	<!-- /ANCHOR:effort -->
   269	
   270	---
   271	
   272	<!-- ANCHOR:enhanced-rollback -->
   273	## L2: ENHANCED ROLLBACK
   274	
   275	### Pre-Cutover Checklist
   276	
   277	- [ ] The retained prior manifest exists for the target hub.
   278	- [ ] The scorer digests match their pinned values.
   279	- [ ] Legacy and compiled routing are equal for the target corpus.
   280	- [ ] The per-hub status readout reports the expected pre-cutover state.
   281	- [ ] `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` has been exercised in the target environment.
   282	
   283	### Rollback Procedure
   284	
   285	1. Set `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` and verify fleet-wide legacy serving.
   286	2. Restore the target hub's retained prior manifest when per-hub authority changed.
   287	3. Restore the previous predicate or directive only for the affected stage.
   288	4. Re-run serving-status, parity, and scorer-integrity gates.
   289	5. Record the failed stage and evidence before another promotion attempt.
   290	
   291	### Data Reversal
   292	
   293	- **Has data migrations?** No persistent user data migration is planned.
   294	- **Reversal procedure**: Configuration and manifest state return to retained prior bytes; diagnostics and reports remain as evidence.
   295	<!-- /ANCHOR:enhanced-rollback -->
