   232	- [ ] Current standalone and parent outputs are captured.
   233	- [ ] No existing hub is targeted for regeneration.
   234	- [ ] P3 interfaces are stable and testable without writing production manifests.
   235	
   236	### Rollback Procedure
   237	
   238	1. Restore prior templates and initializer behavior.
   239	2. Restore legacy as the only reported generated state.
   240	3. Leave any pre-existing canonical manifest untouched and report it for operator reconciliation.
   241	4. Re-run baseline create-skill contract tests.
   242	
   243	### Data Reversal
   244	
   245	- **Has persistent user data changes?** No.
   246	- **Reversal procedure**: Revert generator/template changes; temp test manifests are discarded by the test harness, while real manifests require an explicit operator-owned lifecycle.
