   125	<!-- ANCHOR:phases -->
   126	## 4. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES
   127	
   128	### Phase 1: Setup
   129	
   130	- [ ] Capture frozen hashes, current Lane C reports, verdicts, and exit codes.
   131	- [ ] Pin shared eligibility/status APIs and normalized routing schema.
   132	- [ ] Design temp fixtures for fresh, drifted, missing, broken, and divergent cases without live manifest mutation.
   133	
   134	### Phase 2: Core Implementation
   135	
   136	- [ ] Add `compiled-routing-parity.cjs` with frozen hash verification, child env isolation, normalization, gold evaluation, and equality comparison.
   137	- [ ] Integrate the parity lane into `run-skill-benchmark.cjs` for eligible hub route-gold rows.
   138	- [ ] Add `report.compiledRouting` and distinct verdict/exit handling without changing the score aggregate.
   139	- [ ] Render the report block from JSON in `build-report.cjs`.
   140	- [ ] Document the resolved parity mode and state behavior in README and CLI usage.
   141	
   142	### Phase 3: Verification
   143	
   144	- [ ] Add deterministic Vitest coverage for the full state and routing-shape matrix.
   145	- [ ] Compare post-change legacy D1-D5 reports with baselines.
   146	- [ ] Run the existing Lane C suites plus the new parity suite.
   147	- [ ] Re-hash the frozen files and run strict spec-folder validation.
   148	<!-- /ANCHOR:phases -->
