.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/changelog/v1.3.0.0.md:24:Reviewers occasionally drifted out of role when the rendered prompt was long enough that the role banner scrolled off-screen. The fix injects a `CODE-REVIEW` marker at the start of the rendered-prompt boundary (in the dispatcher YAML, not in reference resources that carry YAML frontmatter where a stray marker would corrupt parsing). The dispatcher then runs a marker-scan step that fails fast if the marker is missing after rendering. This places the role banner where the reviewer is guaranteed to see it without polluting any document that ships frontmatter.
