.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-claude-code/manual-testing-playbook/reasoning-and-models/opus-extended-thinking.md:19:Opus + `--effort high` is the cli-claude-code skill's most expensive dispatch tier and only justified when the depth payoff is real. If Opus + `--effort high` produces output indistinguishable from Sonnet for a multi-dimensional architecture trade-off, the skill's deep-reasoning routing pattern (CC-014, deep-reasoning-delegation in integration-patterns.md) is broken and the cost premium is wasted.
