.opencode/agents/deep-alignment.md:181:  - **Reasoning-agent layer (verify-first)**: for any artifact where a pattern match suggests drift, extract the specific live-behavior claim and re-probe it directly against the real validator, CLI, registry, or source file — never assert a finding from pattern-matching alone (Alignment Invariant 1). When a contradiction is confirmed with cited evidence, construct a finding in the same shape the adapter's own `check()` would produce (`severity`, `type: 'reality-drift'`, `subcheck`, `layer: 'reasoning-agent'`, `message`, artifact identity, `sourceTool: 'live re-probe (agent-performed)'`, `detail: {claim, reprobeEvidence}`) and fold it into this iteration's findings alongside the deterministic-layer output.
.opencode/agents/deep-alignment.md:201:- Do NOT tag findings by review dimension (correctness/security/traceability/maintainability) — that taxonomy does not apply in this mode. Tag each finding by its lane identity (`authority`, `artifactClass`, `scope`) plus the adapter's own `type` / `subcheck` / `layer` fields (for example `template-conformance`/`deterministic`, `reality-alignment`/`reasoning-agent`, `commit-message-grammar`/`deterministic`, `live-render-judgment`/`reasoning-agent`). Findings classification in this mode is per-lane, never per-dimension.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.6.0.md:33:- **`--variant`**: maps to MiMo's reasoning effort (low/medium/high) in opencode settings; **always dispatch with `--variant high`** (confirmed accepted on opencode 1.15.13; operator-directed standing default).
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.6.0.md:46:- The framework benchmark was **re-run at `--variant high`** for both MiMo and MiniMax (a 2×2: model × default/high). **COSTAR holds as co-winner for MiMo at high reasoning** — at high the field *compresses* (even TIDD-EC's verbosity penalty largely vanishes: 151→66 words on the hard fixture; format-adherent frameworks went 2/5→4/5), so framework choice matters *less* at high reasoning, but COSTAR/RACE-lean stays the safe default. MiniMax → RACE on this 2-fixture rig — do NOT overwrite the 7-fixture 120/003 TIDD-EC recommendation (correctness saturates on 2 tractable fixtures). Framework (COSTAR) and reasoning (`--variant high`) are independent, composable levers.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.6.0.md:52:- Benchmark (default reasoning): `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/126-cli-opencode-mimo-pro-optimization/004-mimo-prompt-framework-benchmark/eval/synthesis.md`
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.3.6.0.md:53:- Benchmark (`--variant high` 2×2 re-run): `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/126-cli-opencode-mimo-pro-optimization/004-mimo-prompt-framework-benchmark/eval/synthesis-high-reasoning.md`
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-claude-code/references/agent-delegation.md:35:- Deep reasoning and extended thinking via `@ai-council`
