.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:1:This release restructures the cli-opencode provider surface to match the operator's actual `opencode providers list` output: three providers (`github-copilot`, `opencode-go`, `deepseek`) instead of the previous five-way Anthropic/OpenAI/Google/opencode-go/deepseek mix. The canonical default flips from `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro` to `github-copilot/gpt-5.4 --variant high` so dispatches resolve cleanly under the Copilot OAuth boundary which is pre-authenticated for users with an active subscription. Copilot models named in the skill are scoped to two (`gpt-5.4` default, `claude-sonnet-4.6` alternative); the DeepSeek direct API is trimmed to `deepseek-v4-pro` (reasoning) and `deepseek-v4-flash` (latency).
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:11:The skill default routes through GitHub Copilot's `gpt-5.4` at high reasoning effort. Copilot ships pre-authenticated for active subscribers and exposes the broadest model surface (Claude / GPT variants) under one OAuth token, removing the per-provider login friction that the previous `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro` default depended on. `gpt-5.4` accepts the full GPT variant range (`minimal / low / medium / high / xhigh`) so the existing `--variant high` posture carries over without behavioral change. Default switched from `gpt-5.5` to `gpt-5.4` mid-release to match the cli-copilot default and reflect operator preference.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:19:The Copilot model surface advertised in the skill is intentionally narrow: `gpt-5.4` (default) and `claude-sonnet-4.6` (Anthropic alternative for code review and balanced reasoning). The full Copilot lineup (opus / haiku / additional GPT / Grok variants) remains reachable via `--model github-copilot/<id>` overrides but is not surfaced in the skill's tables to keep the documented surface focused.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:23:`deepseek/deepseek-reasoner` and `deepseek/deepseek-chat` are dropped from the model selection tables and override examples. The direct DeepSeek API surface (which bypasses opencode-go) keeps `deepseek-v4-pro` (reasoning effort accepted) and `deepseek-v4-flash` (non-reasoning sibling). Provider-isolation testing in CO-011 still validates that `deepseek/` and `opencode-go/` are independent surfaces, not aliases.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:32:- `004-variant-levels-comparison.md` — variant cap table dropped Anthropic/OpenAI/Google rows; now lists `github-copilot/gpt-5.4` (xhigh), `github-copilot/claude-sonnet-4.6` (max), `opencode-go/deepseek-v4-pro` (provider-specific), `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro` (reasoning effort accepted).
