.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/reasoning-effort/medium-skill-default.md:2:title: "CX-010 -- medium reasoning (skill default)"
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/reasoning-effort/medium-skill-default.md:3:description: "This scenario validates the medium reasoning level as the documented skill default for `CX-010`. It focuses on confirming explicit medium dispatches succeed and align with SKILL.md §3."
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/reasoning-effort/medium-skill-default.md:7:# CX-010 -- medium reasoning (skill default)
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/reasoning-effort/medium-skill-default.md:15:This scenario validates the `medium` reasoning level as the documented skill default for `CX-010`. It focuses on confirming `medium` is the documented default and that two explicit-medium dispatches produce equivalent behavior on a standard code-generation task.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/reasoning-effort/medium-skill-default.md:19:SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule 7 mandates that the model + effort + service tier be passed explicitly on every invocation. `medium` is the documented default. This scenario keeps the explicit-effort discipline honest by requiring the operator to dispatch with `-c model_reasoning_effort="medium"` even when the result would be the same as omitting it.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/reasoning-effort/medium-skill-default.md:27:- Objective: Verify `medium` is the documented skill default reasoning effort and that two explicit-medium dispatches produce equivalent code-generation output.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/reasoning-effort/medium-skill-default.md:28:- Real user request: `Run the documented default reasoning level twice on the same prompt and confirm consistency.`
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/reasoning-effort/medium-skill-default.md:29:- Prompt: `Run the clamp utility prompt twice at medium reasoning and confirm both outputs are comparable and explicitly flagged medium.`
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/reasoning-effort/medium-skill-default.md:30:- Expected execution process: Operator dispatches the same prompt twice with `-c model_reasoning_effort="medium"` explicit on both -> captures both outputs -> compares them at a high level (same function signature, similar behavior) -> records a brief equivalence note.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/reasoning-effort/medium-skill-default.md:31:- Expected signals: Both invocations exit 0. Both produce a small TypeScript utility (e.g., a `clamp(n, min, max)` function). Both dispatched command lines include `-c model_reasoning_effort="medium"` explicitly per SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule 7. Outputs are functionally equivalent.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/reasoning-effort/medium-skill-default.md:33:- Pass/fail: PASS if both invocations exit 0, both produce a TypeScript `clamp` function, both dispatched command lines include the explicit `-c model_reasoning_effort="medium"` flag, AND the operator records an equivalence note. FAIL if either invocation fails or omits the explicit flag.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/reasoning-effort/medium-skill-default.md:41:1. Dispatch the prompt twice with explicit `-c model_reasoning_effort="medium"` on both invocations.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/manual-testing-playbook/reasoning-effort/medium-skill-default.md:49:| CX-010 | medium reasoning (skill default) | Verify medium reasoning is the documented skill default and produces consistent output | `Run the clamp utility prompt twice at medium reasoning and confirm both outputs are comparable and explicitly flagged medium.` | 1. `codex exec --model gpt-5.5 -c model_reasoning_effort="medium" -c service_tier="fast" --sandbox read-only "Output ONLY a TypeScript function: clamp(n: number, min: number, max: number): number that returns n clamped to the [min, max] range. No explanation." > /tmp/cli-codex-cx010-run1.ts 2>&1` -> 2. `codex exec --model gpt-5.5 -c model_reasoning_effort="medium" -c service_tier="fast" --sandbox read-only "Output ONLY a TypeScript function: clamp(n: number, min: number, max: number): number that returns n clamped to the [min, max] range. No explanation." > /tmp/cli-codex-cx010-run2.ts 2>&1` -> 3. `bash: grep -E "function clamp\|clamp.*=.*\(\|clamp\(" /tmp/cli-codex-cx010-run1.ts /tmp/cli-codex-cx010-run2.ts > /tmp/cli-codex-cx010-grep.txt` -> 4. `bash: printf 'EQUIVALENCE: both runs produced a clamp function with the documented signature; both invocations passed -c model_reasoning_effort="medium" explicitly per SKILL.md §4 ALWAYS rule 7.\n' > /tmp/cli-codex-cx010-note.txt` | Steps 1-2: both exit 0, both stdout files contain a TypeScript `clamp` function; Step 3: grep finds `clamp` in both files with the expected signature; Step 4: equivalence note created | Two captured TypeScript files, the grep output, the equivalence note, two dispatched command lines, exit codes | PASS if both exit 0, both contain `clamp` with the right signature, both command lines have the explicit `-c model_reasoning_effort="medium"` flag, AND the equivalence note exists; FAIL if any check misses | (1) Confirm SKILL.md §3 still names `medium` as the default; (2) re-run with `2>&1 \| tee` for stderr inline; (3) inspect both `.ts` files manually for divergent semantics |
