.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:8:  - "codex reasoning effort"
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:26:Codex CLI is OpenAI's terminal-based AI coding agent powered by `gpt-5.5` — a balanced model used across code generation, review, architecture analysis, and research. The skill dispatches `gpt-5.5` at `medium` reasoning on the `fast` service tier by default; users can override reasoning effort (e.g. "Use gpt 5.5 high fast"). It provides direct access to OpenAI's capabilities from the command line, including code generation, file manipulation, shell execution, web browsing, and multi-turn sessions — all governed by configurable sandbox modes.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:98:| `--model` | `-m` | `gpt-5.5` | Model to use — `gpt-5.5` (default), `gpt-5.6-luna`, `gpt-5.6-terra`, `gpt-5.6-sol` |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:99:| `--config` | `-c` | `key=value` | Override a config.toml value (e.g., `-c model_reasoning_effort="high"`) |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:136:# Override reasoning effort
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:137:codex exec "Analyze this architecture" -m gpt-5.5 -c model_reasoning_effort="high"
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:143:codex exec "Task" -c model_reasoning_effort="xhigh" -c sandbox_mode="read-only"
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:183:Four GPT models are callable on the `fast` service tier via `--model` / `-m`. `gpt-5.5` at `medium` is the skill default; each model caps at a different reasoning-effort ceiling.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:188:| **GPT-5.6 LUNA** | `gpt-5.6-luna` | `max` | Implementation-heavy work; the `luna-impl` profile pins `max` |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:189:| **GPT-5.6 TERRA** | `gpt-5.6-terra` | `max` | GPT-5.6 fast sibling; no dedicated profile — call directly via `-m gpt-5.6-terra` |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:190:| **GPT-5.6 SOL** | `gpt-5.6-sol` | `ultra` | Verification / review and hardest planning; only model reaching `ultra` (the `sol-verify` profile pins `xhigh`) |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:194:Reasoning effort controls how much "thinking" the model does. There is **no `--reasoning-effort` CLI flag**. Set it via:
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:196:1. **CLI override:** `-c model_reasoning_effort="high"`
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:197:2. **config.toml:** `model_reasoning_effort = "medium"` (global default matching the skill)
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:198:3. **Profile:** `[profiles.review]` → `model_reasoning_effort = "xhigh"`
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:199:4. **Plan mode:** `plan_mode_reasoning_effort = "medium"` (Plan-mode-specific override)
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:205:| `none` | No reasoning — fastest, lowest cost | all |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:206:| `minimal` | Minimal reasoning | all |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:207:| `low` | Low reasoning effort | all |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:208:| `medium` | Standard reasoning (skill default) | all |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:209:| `high` | High reasoning effort | all |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:210:| `xhigh` | Deep reasoning — ceiling for `gpt-5.5` | all |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:211:| `max` | Deeper reasoning — `gpt-5.6-luna` / `gpt-5.6-terra` / `gpt-5.6-sol` | 5.6 family |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:212:| `ultra` | Deepest reasoning — `gpt-5.6-sol` only | `gpt-5.6-sol` |
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:228:Always specify `--model` explicitly in scripts for predictability (`gpt-5.5` is the skill default); omitting it relies on the CLI default, which may change across versions. When a task wants reasoning past `xhigh`, escalate the model: `--model gpt-5.6-luna -c model_reasoning_effort="max"` for deep implementation, `--model gpt-5.6-sol -c model_reasoning_effort="ultra"` for the hardest verification/review.
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:233:# Reasoning-heavy tasks — raise reasoning_effort
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:234:codex exec "Analyze this architecture and identify coupling issues" --model gpt-5.5 -c model_reasoning_effort="high"
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:235:codex exec "Security audit of @./src/auth.ts" --model gpt-5.5 -c model_reasoning_effort="high"
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:238:codex exec "Write unit tests for user.ts" --model gpt-5.5 -c model_reasoning_effort="medium"
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:239:codex exec "Generate a rate limiter middleware" --model gpt-5.5 -c model_reasoning_effort="medium"
.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-codex/references/cli-reference.md:245:# .codex/agents/my-agent.toml — reasoning-heavy agent
