   150	
   151	---
   152	
   153	<!-- ANCHOR:limitations -->
   154	## Known Limitations
   155	
   156	1. **The ruling is reversible and overridable.** The settled phased path is a documentation decision; the operator may override to flip-now, and no runtime state depends on the ruling yet.
   157	2. **The flag is still undocumented in the environment reference.** That gap is P0 implementation work, not work performed by this authoring phase.
   158	3. **Drift and breakage are not yet distinguishable in the live verification surface.** The planned P0 harness change owns that distinction.
   159	4. **Eligibility is still duplicated.** The P3 implementation has not replaced the current hand-maintained sets.
   160	5. **The resolver still depends on the current runtime path arrangement.** P0 must promote it or record and guard an approved exception.
   161	<!-- /ANCHOR:limitations -->
   162	
   163	---
   164	
   165	<!-- ANCHOR:follow-up -->
   166	## Follow-ups
   167	
