.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/009-non-hub-rollout/002-system-code-graph/implementation-summary.md:98:1. Shadow parity is not zero-mismatch. The legacy router returns two selected leaves for equal evidence and empty observations for defer/reject, while the compiled algebra emits typed clarify/defer/reject. All three differences are classified and effect-free; live activation remains deferred.
